Lyeurgus, -i, m. Lycurgus, king of Thrace. He tried to expel Dionysus from his realm, and drove him into the sea, where Thetis received him. Zeus in anger blinded Lycurgus, who died soon after. According to other tradi- tions Dionysus drove him mad, and he killed his son, and cut off one of his legs, thinking it to be a vine. The country was then stricken with barren- ness, and the Edonians took Lycurgus to Mt. Pangaeum„ where he was torn asunder by horses.
